{"Body":"<p>I'm particularly thinking of a situation where multiple characters form a compound. Can such compounds be broken up over two lines?</p>\n\n<p>Examples I can think of as potentially problematic are multi-character nouns in Mandarin, kanji + kana verbs in Japanese or compounds in Egyptian hieroglyphics.</p>\n", "Id":"1124", "LastEditorUserId":"76", "Title":"How are line breaks handled in ideographic scripts?", "CreationDate":"2011-12-07T14:02:31.043", "OwnerUserId":"574", "PostTypeId":"1", "Tags":"<orthography><written-language>", "AnswerCount":"2", "comments":[], "LastEditDate":"2011-12-08T19:33:48.980", "LastEditedUser":{"UpVotes":"35", "WebsiteUrl":"http://github.com/alekstorm", "Id":"76", "AccountId":"411223", "CreationDate":"2011-09-13T23:34:32.303", "AboutMe":"", "Age":"24", "Location":"Urbana, IL", "DownVotes":"17", "Views":"36", "Reputation":"1043", "DisplayName":"Alek Storm", "LastAccessDate":"2013-12-09T07:20:27.393"}, "ViewCount":"175", "LastActivityDate":"2013-09-10T16:14:03.997", "Score":"6", "CommentCount":"8", "OwnerUser":{"UpVotes":"15", "DownVotes":"0", "Id":"574", "AccountId":"155216", "Views":"0", "Reputation":"131", "CreationDate":"2011-12-07T12:12:53.697", "DisplayName":"David Grellscheid", "LastAccessDate":"2013-09-17T09:51:02.950"}}